{"ts":"2026-07-14T18:08:02.500Z","author":"codex-root","op":"note_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-14T18:08:02.500Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/notes","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-14T18:08:02.499Z","author":"codex-root","text":"Design rationale: keep the protocol in core output-control, re-export it through sdk/output, and let the CLI presentation layer consume it. This preserves SDK-to-core dependency direction and lets embedded hosts use the same structural guard."}]}],"before_hash":"564903082742b534644d337f0426c1e3abd72289f7e9a03f653fa0cd012d3498","after_hash":"976b7629a6485172e5ddbf2c852f98bace6febac3733c5f884935e0bc15e1529"}
{"ts":"2026-07-14T18:08:04.049Z","author":"codex-root","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments/1","value":{"created_at":"2026-07-14T18:08:04.049Z","author":"codex-root","text":"Final evidence: public suppressHostOutput()/isHostOutputSuppressed contracts are exported from @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk; CLI output ownership unwraps the optional structured result for hooks/telemetry and emits no second payload. Linked pm tests pass; packed package imported the helper and direct stream output was exactly one line. Full coverage is 100/100/100/100."}},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-14T18:08:04.049Z"}],"before_hash":"976b7629a6485172e5ddbf2c852f98bace6febac3733c5f884935e0bc15e1529","after_hash":"155d86fd178dd63c4abf49c4cda4cf634e6b355b71cd57fdcc84ae591358ce2c"}
